&#8216;Fast &amp; Furious 8&#8217; collected Rs 10 crore on Saturday (Day 3) taking its total to about Rs 36 crore, as reported by Boxofficeindia.com. The film had opened on Thursday at Rs 9.25 crore and went on to collect Rs 11.25 crore on Friday. In addition, the action film had earned Rs 5.50 crore from paid previews on Wednesday.Featuring Vin Diesel, Dwayne Johnson, Jason Statham, Michelle Rodriguez, Tyrese Gibson, Chris &#8216;Ludacris&#8217; Bridges, Scott Eastwood, Nathalie Emmanuel, Kurt Russell and the new addition Charlize Theron, the film is the eighth installment in &#8216;The Fast and the Furious&#8217; franchise. Loaded with nail-biting action and car-chasing scenes, it delivers all that the action series is known for.Directed by F. Gary Gray and written by Chris Morgan, &#8216;Fast &amp; Furious 8&#8217; is the first film of the franchise that does not feature Paul Walker, who died in a tragic car crash in the middle of production of &#8216;Furious 7&#8217; (2015).This article first appeared on Times of India 